	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's cool to see this technique in pixel action! It looks pretty nice. <br /><br />Since the water is moving, i think it makes sense if the surface waves dictate the turbulence underneath (which it does in most cases, but not all). I put my thumbs on the screen and compared column for column until i found the one piece that felt a bit off. It does a -180 degree opposite at one place. It might look more natural if this is more or less phase reverted. Not saying definitely, but could be worth a try. It could also turn out too mechanical, which in case could be remedied if a higher frame budget is allowed, by allowing a light part lag one frame behind in, say, a 6 or 8 frame cycle.<br /><br /><br />For river purposes, any of your previous blue and white ones look convincing to me.

		

		</td>
